sharedPost.text: Casting for Women age 35 to 75 who really love to take care of their skin and have made bold choices that changed their lives for the better. Paid for those selected for the campaign ¬£3.5 K. These stories could include things like changing their career to something they love, heading off on a solo adventure, starting a new business, building something beautiful in their community, navigating a health journey, a late bloomer artist or maker, A mother who has navigated IVF or fertility or become a parent later in life, someone who has made a big decision- like leaving a job or a relationship to choose themselves, someone who has gone from terrified of the gym. and sport to feeling so confident, someone learning a new skill, someone who has become a financial expert in finance, health or something really difficult. Filming will take place early to mid January. Everyone will be needed for 2 days. The campaign will be live for 3 months  online/ social/ web/ retail, print ( leaflets included with purchase only) TV billboards/ POS 1 shoot day with videographer filming at a location related to your story and 1 shoot day in a studio w/c 12th Jan.They may also want to include photos and videos of you demonstrating your game changing journey. Lastly they might ask for people to be filmed to see their reactions on a bill board!this is TBC. If this brief resonates with you please email me hello@casscasting.com Thank you

Join us and grow together in the fastest-rising livestream e-commerce market in North America!

üé¨ Job Responsibilities:
 ‚Ä¢ Host livestream shows on the Whatnot platform to showcase and sell products (categories depend on the store such as fashion/beauty/collectibles/home goods, etc.)
 ‚Ä¢ Prepare product scripts and selling points before each show; assist in improving livestream procedures
 ‚Ä¢ Interact with viewers, answer questions, and create an engaging atmosphere to increase conversion
 ‚Ä¢ Work with the team on livestream reviews and traffic optimization

‚ú® We‚Äôre Looking for Someone Who:
 ‚Ä¢ Has livestreaming experience (any platform such as TikTok / YouTube / IG Live, etc.)
 ‚Ä¢ Outgoing, energetic, and enjoys engaging with people
 ‚Ä¢ Has good image and strong on-camera presence
 ‚Ä¢ Is fluent in spoken English and capable of hosting in English
 ‚Ä¢ Is eager to learn and grow in the livestream e-commerce industry
 ‚Ä¢ Is legally eligible to work in the U.S.

üìç Location:
Los Angeles (Remote or On-site depending on position needs)

‚è± Schedule:
3‚Äì6 livestream sessions per week; flexible hours negotiable

üí∞ Compensation:
Base salary + Performance commission + Bonuses
High performers enjoy rapid growth and unlimited income potential!

üéØ Preferred Qualifications (Not Required):
 ‚Ä¢ Sales experience in fashion, beauty, or related categories
 ‚Ä¢ Styling sense / trend awareness
 ‚Ä¢ Skills in video editing, content planning, and streaming metrics to showcase

üì© How to Apply:
Please send your resume + a short self-introduction video and/or previous livestream links to:
hzhong@thunderex.com
Email subject: Whatnot Host + Your Name

üåü If you love being on camera and want to grow with a passionate team,
we want YOU to become our next livestream star! üåü

SHARING PAID OPPORTUNITY 

I‚Äôm Jude, casting with Liz Lewis Casting Partners, and I wanted to share a current project we‚Äôre working on for Metamucil.

For this particular project, we are actually looking for real Metamucil users, ages 45‚Äì60, with no professional acting or performing experience. While we know this community is full of talented actors, we wanted to share here in case you might know friends, family members, or people in your network who could be a great fit.

It‚Äôs a nationwide search. The shoot location is still being finalized and may be Austin, or possibly Mexico or Canada. If travel is required, production will cover all travel and accommodations.

Compensation is $500 per shoot day, plus $3,400 for 1-year usage, all media.

**Participants cannot have any professional performing experience, including paid acting, dancing, or singing work (union or non-union). **

To submit please click on this link [Metamucil Form](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSffQ4Zl_-5Evj8FE5NNi9aTaYuc-htYG1gLG25xmTIcI_CM4g/viewform?usp=header)

If this sounds like you or someone you know, feel free to reach out or share!

Hallo Zusammen,

mein Name ist Willi, ich bin 30 Jahre alt, arbeite als Senior Management Consultant bei einer internationalen Steuerberatungs- und Wirtschaftspr√ºfungsgesellschaft, bin nebenbei Unternehmer ‚Äì und trage seit meiner Kindheit eine gro√üe Leidenschaft in mir: Film & Schauspiel.

Schon damals haben mich Geschichten, komplexe Charaktere und starke Bilder fasziniert. W√§hrend meines Studiums durfte ich bereits an einem Independent-Filmprojekt mitwirken, und dieses Feuer ist √ºber die Jahre immer gr√∂√üer geworden. Jetzt ist f√ºr mich der Zeitpunkt gekommen, mich vor der Kamera auszuprobieren und diesen Weg zu verfolgen.

Ich beginne aktuell mit hochwertigem Schauspielunterricht, unter anderem bei Lehrern, die an renommierten Universit√§ten in den USA ausgebildet wurden.

Ich liebe es, mich tief in Rollen hineinzudenken, Charaktere authentisch umzusetzen und sie exzellent performen zu lassen. Hierbei bin ich sehr selbstkritisch, reflektierend, detailverliebt und habe hohe Anspr√ºche an mich selbst. Auch f√ºr Szenenbild und Atmosph√§re habe ich ein gutes Gesp√ºr ‚Äì ich gehe vollkommen in kreativer Arbeit auf.

Daher w√ºrde ich mich sehr freuen, in spannenden Projekten mitzuwirken ‚Äì gerne auch No-Budget und in ‚ÄûNebenrollen‚Äú, denn das ist meine gro√üe Leidenschaft.

Wenn ihr Unterst√ºtzung sucht, meldet euch sehr gerne bei mir. Ich freue mich auf den Austausch und darauf, gemeinsam Geschichten zum Leben zu erwecken.

Beste Gr√º√üe,

Willi

Hey, 

Im Sam, I‚Äôm 34 years old and based in the north west of England. A little place called the Ribble valley and I‚Äôm trying to build up my portfolio by working on different projects to show case my acting skills. 

I am actively training and developing my craft by attending acting classes at Cartwright‚Äôs Drama Studios, expanding my skills in screen acting, improvisation, and character work. I am committed, reliable, and eager to gain further experience in professional environments.

Please see my most recent headshots I‚Äôm open to a variety of roles and would be excited to collaborate on new projects. Looking forward to connecting with anyone who feels I might suit their casting needs.

Thanks Sam x

Hallo ihr Lieben,

ich arbeite an einem Projekt, in dem ich Menschen interviewe, die mit unsichtbaren oder wenig bekannten Krankheiten leben ‚Äì also Erkrankungen, die man nicht auf den ersten Blick sieht, die aber trotzdem den Alltag stark beeinflussen.

Mir ist wichtig, diesen Menschen eine Stimme zu geben: zu zeigen, was sie erleben, wie sie sich f√ºhlen und was sich in unserer Gesellschaft vielleicht ver√§ndern sollte.

Wenn du selbst betroffen bist oder jemanden kennst, der mit einer solchen Krankheit lebt und offen dar√ºber sprechen m√∂chte, melde dich gerne bei mir.
Das Gespr√§ch kann auf Wunsch anonym stattfinden.

Ich freue mich √ºber jede Nachricht, jedes Vertrauen und jede Geschichte ‚Äì ob gro√ü oder klein.

Liebe Gr√º√üe
Polly

items.title: Hallo ihr Lieben,

items.text:
Location: Berlin

Shooting: mid-January

None paid (student project) + food + footage reel

ROLE HELEN (Lead, playing age 23-30)

Helen is the daughter of Hades, living in the mortal world in isolation.

She‚Äôs observant, emotionally detached on the surface, but with a complex inner world.

Her energy is quiet, intense, and unpredictable; she feels outside of humanity while desperately

studying it.

She is not a stereotype ‚Äústrong female lead‚Äù.

She is layered, morally grey, dry, curious, bitter, vulnerable, and intimidating without trying.

A character who barely shows her emotions but feels everything deeply.

This role requires:

‚óè strong subtle acting

‚óè microexpressions

‚óè comfort with psychological + mystical scenes

‚óè ability to play someone who is always scanning her surroundings

‚óè comfort acting opposite horror elements (no gore, more psychological/supernatural)

No previous fantasy experience needed, just strong emotional control and complexity.

All ethnicities welcome.

ABOUT THE PROJECT 

This is a 30-minute TV pilot for my graduation project and a proof-of-concept.

The tone is similar to The Sandman, Pan‚Äôs Labyrinth, and Only Lovers Left Alive; dark, poetic,

mythological, grounded in emotional realism.

The story explores:

‚óè Mythology incorporated into modern Berlin

‚óè Identity and isolation

‚óè Power structures

‚óè Neurodivergent perception

‚óè The horror of being watched by the divine

Helen is the center of this world.

We offer a complex role with depth and high-quality footage for your acting reel. As stated

before, this is a proof-of-concept pilot episode. The goal is to apply for further funding and production support in 2026 and continue the series.

REQUIREMENTS

‚óè Based in Berlin or able to travel.

‚óè Availability for shooting in mid-January.

‚óè Comfortable with night scenes and horror tones.

‚óè Able to commit to rehearsals in December.

TO APPLY!!

Send to: celia.t@catalyst-students.com

‚óè Recent headshot or clear photo.

‚óè Showreel (if available).

‚óè Your age + where you are based.

items.text:
Hallo liebe Freunde der Musik

Am 05.12.2025 erscheint unser Song HIMMEL AUF ERDEN auf Spotify und allen anderen Musik-Streaming-Platformen.

H√∂rt gerne mal rein, erz√§hlt es weiter und rockt das Sofa.

Himmel auf Erden 

Du warst der Himmel auf Erden, ich der Regen, der verwirrt auf uns f√§llt.

Eine Liebe, die nicht verstanden, auf wunderbare Weise gelebt und ausradiert wird.

Dieser Rocksong symbolisiert eine Reise durch H√∂hen und Tiefen, mal laut, mal leise,

vom Winde verweht, in Gedanken versunken, intensiv gelebt, nehme ich dich mit... pack den Rucksack voller Erinnerung und komm mit!

 Eure DiMiKA CRUNCH-POP¬Æ

items.text:
CASTING CALL ‚Äì STARFARM 

We‚Äôre casting fun, stylish young women (15‚Äì25) for an unscripted eco-reality series!

AI is taking over the world. Replacing jobs, replacing people, reforming industries. They are humanity's greatest creation yet our ultimate competition. Now, an unscripted eco-reality series featuring 10 young women, learning to live on a completely remote and self-sustainable farm - across the dirt road, lies another self-sustained farm; run by AI. Will they survive or thrive? Will they change the future for the next generation of girls, by proving something woman-powered can be more fruitful than something AI-powered?

Do you have :
* 
**STRONG SENSE OF PERSONAL STYLE AND CREATIVE CONFIDENCE**
*

items.text:
## **Casting Breakdown: *****OUROBOROS***

A Psychological Horror film. The Fourth Film from Pineal Dreams Productions.

‚ÄúWhen a young couple suffer the pain of a miscarriage; they retreat to a cottage in the woods to try and heal. Unfortunately they quickly discover that you can never run away from your trauma‚Äô

**üéì Lead Roles**

**AMAIA**

**Female | Playing age: 20-30 | Ethnicity: Open**

 **Description:** A young woman, grief-stricken, haunted by a recent miscarriage. Intelligent, emotionally complex, volatile, and deeply human. Fluctuates between tender vulnerability and violent dissociation.

 **Performance notes:** Requires a wide emotional range ‚Äî subtle detachment, raw grief, moments of horror, as well as serenity towards the end.  Appears in nearly every scene.

 **Comparable roles:** Charlotte Gainsbourg (*Antichrist*), Essie Davis (*The Babadook*), Jennifer Connelly *(Requiem for a Dream), *Isabelle Adjani *(Possession)*

This is a dual-role as they will also be playing the character of Amaia‚Äôs Doppelganger

**AMAIA'S DOPPELGANGER **

**Female | Same actor as Amaia preferred**

 **Description:** An uncanny mirror of Amaia ‚Äî at times gentle, at times mocking or malevolent. Not a "villain" but an emotional specter. She represents Amaia‚Äôs true opinion of herself, and pulls at her mental fragility to attempt to make her finally give in to her pain.

 **Performance notes:** If dual casting is not possible, physical resemblance and matched acting style are key. The role is symbolic and dreamlike.

 **Type:** Similar movement to Amaia, but with a more ‚Äòfloaty‚Äô and ethereal feel to it.

The nature of a dual role would suit an actress who really wants a challenge - as well as the maximum amount of screen time for any character in the film. Hopefully, a brilliant showcase role for talent who want to establish themselves as a critically respected performer, as they will be carrying the vast bulk of the film‚Äôs emotional core.

We aim to film a bulk of the filming in one five-day block, with three scenes needing filming elsewhere. We anticipate filming will require ten days, with one day of ADR needed for additional dialogue/audio fixes.

We know it‚Äôs frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

PAID - A minimal fee. Which can be discussed upon application. This is our fourth short-film, and the first we‚Äôve offered payment for. It was a late decision, as we appreciate experience doesn‚Äôt pay the rent. However, being a tiny, self-funded studio, it is a relatively small amount.

All food and transport - and accommodation, if needed - also covered.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That‚Äôs our promise to you.

**DONN**

**Male | Playing age: 30-40 | Ethnicity: Open**

**Description:** Amaia‚Äôs partner. Kind, supportive, but emotionally shut down. A man attempting to cope through suppression - a misguided attempt at stoicism as he believes she must be strong to support Amaia - whose quiet unraveling becomes key to the resolution.

 **Performance notes:** Understated emotionality. Requires physical performance (injury, crawling, etc.) and strong presence in silence.

 **Comparable roles:** Michael Fassbender (*Shame*), Mads Mikkelsen (*Another Round*), Javier Bardem *(Mother!)*, Harry Dean Stanton *(Paris, Texas)*

Filming block will be the same as Amaia‚Äôs. Five-day block (Hopefully), as well as shoots at just three other locations.Ten days of filming maximum, but this could always change if re-shoots are necessary, and one day of ADR work will be required.

We know it‚Äôs frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

PAID - A minimal fee. Which can be discussed upon application. This is our fourth short-film, and the first we‚Äôve offered payment for. It was a late decision, as we appreciate experience doesn‚Äôt pay the rent. However, being a tiny, self-funded studio, it is a relatively small amount.

All food and transport - and accommodation, if needed - also covered.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That‚Äôs our promise to you.

**üë• Supporting Roles -**

**THE UMBRA**

**Male | Playing age: ANY | Tall, slender, distinctive presence | Ethnicity: Open**

 **Description:** A silent manifestation of trauma that watches over and manipulates events ‚Äî a mythic observer of Amaia‚Äôs trauma. Symbol of death, memory, or fate.

 **Performance notes:** No dialogue for a vast majority of the script, though requires a sequence of some very carnival-esque dialogue. Face never seen. Must convey gravitas, mystery, and quiet threat through stillness and gaze.

 **Type:** Dancer, mime, or physical performer backgrounds welcomed. Could even opt for the possibility of a physical performer, and a separate voice-actor. So any voice-actors interested, please feel free to contact us.

Similar Roles: Doug Jones (Pan‚Äôs Labyrinth), Tim Purcell (The Babadook), Javier Botet (Slenderman)

The Umbra appears in the Cottage and scenes surrounding it, all of which will be filmed during the scheduled five-day filming block.

There will also be one additional day, in which you will be required for a single scene that takes place in a different location.

Re-shoots are of course always possible, and will be needed for one ADR session for dialogue provided during an animated sequence.

PAID - But a smaller fee than Amaia/Donn as will be required for less days.  This can be discussed upon application. We aim to film a bulk of the filming in one five-day block, with one scene needing filming elsewhere. We anticipate filming will require tsix days, with one day of ADR needed for additional dialogue/audio fixes.

We know it‚Äôs frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That‚Äôs our promise to you.

We are a very small studio, and this is our fourth short. However, our mantra has always been a ‚Äòquality over quantity‚Äô approach. We take great pride in not just making a film, but really thinking it through on a technical level. We appreciate classic and arthouse cinema, and are far more interested in making a good film than red carpet events.

Our three shorts so far have been screened at over 20 festivals, picking up around 14 awards - including two IMDB qualified awards. (best actor for Jackson Wright in Inside The Abyss). Our latest film has seen our lead - Tash Morley - pick up three awards. We aim for this to be our best film yet.

If interested in the roles, please contact me directly via the Pineal Dreams Instagram page. My own personal profiles - both Joshua Moulini√© (Facebook/Instagram). Or Email me directly on [Moulinie23@gmail.com](mailto:Moulinie23@gmail.com)

We hope to hear from you all very soon!

items.text:
Here's a Sneak Peek. PROLOGUE ‚Äî SHADOWS AIN‚ÄôT SILENT Night hangs low over the city like a hood pulled tight. Streetlights flicker ‚Äî tired eyes refusing to sleep. Somewhere a siren weeps into the dark, echoing a truth nobody admits: On this block, quiet is never peace. Quiet is set-up. A figure moves through alley steam ‚Äî slow, controlled, like violence wearing sneakers. Cigarette glow pulses like a heartbeat refusing to die. Every corner whispers Marcus Reed‚Äôs name. Not loud. Not proud. Tentative. Afraid. Up above, a rooftop door cracks open. A shadow watches. Patient. Hungry. A text vibrates in Marcus‚Äôs pocket. Private number. No contact picture. Three words: YOU‚ÄôRE NEXT. Marcus doesn‚Äôt freeze. He‚Äôs been next his whole life. He crushes the cigarette against brick. Smoke ghosts away. Concrete groans under his boots.  Somewhere, a window shuts like a secret learning to keep itself. The block inhales. Marcus exhales. Game‚Äôs already started. Welcome back. CHAPTER 1 ‚Äì WAREHOUSE SHADOWS Part 1: Smoke and Steel The camera glides low across a warehouse floor slick with oil stains and cigarette butts. Fluorescent lights flicker overhead like they‚Äôre on their last breath. Stacks of cocaine bricks sit wrapped tight in plastic, piled high like cursed treasure. The soundtrack hums low: a heavy bass line, thumping slow, like a heartbeat that knows something‚Äôs coming. Marcus Reed steps into frame. The glow of his blunt lights his face for half a second‚Äîhard jaw, eyes sharp, smoke curling like whispers. Goons move in the background. One seals bags. Another slams diesel truck doors shut. Rifles glint in the half-light. ‚ÄúCount it twice,‚Äù Marcus mutters, his voice steady but cold. ‚ÄúLast man that shorted me ain‚Äôt walking no more.‚Äù The room stills for a beat. Even the scales seem louder as the numbers flicker green. He taps ash, scans rafters, notes the ladder that wasn‚Äôt there yesterday. A fan ticks, off rhythm, like a bad omen with loose screws. Camera pushes in on Marcus‚Äôs hands‚Äîscarred, sure, calm like street weather. He doesn‚Äôt blink when a pallet pops; he only shifts his weight and smiles without joy, the smile you practice when danger starts spelling your name in smoke. Tonight. Part 2: The Silent Weigh-In Close-up: hands, rough and scarred, sliding kilo after kilo onto digital scales. Each beep cuts the silence sharper than a blade. Marcus circles the table like a director on set. Every move, every breath, he watches. ‚ÄúBag tighter,‚Äù he snaps at one goon fumbling with tape. ‚ÄúYou leave air in there, you might as well sign your death certificate.‚Äù The man nods fast, sweat running down his temple. Overhead shot: crates stacked against the wall. A shadow moves in the rafters. Quick cut‚Äîgone before anyone notices. The bass in the soundtrack climbs higher. A stopwatch clicks. Numbers glow cold on a wall clock that‚Äôs always three minutes fast; Marcus keeps it that way, likes getting to trouble before trouble gets to him. He lifts a brick, squeezes, listens for that soft crunch that tells the truth. It purrs. He nods. The camera lingers on a scale drifting a gram, drifting back‚Äîlike it‚Äôs breathing. ‚ÄúSwap it,‚Äù he orders. ‚ÄúBad lungs.‚Äù A forklift coughs awake then dies. Somewhere a phone vibrates. Marcus inhales, tastes plastic and promise. He holds the exhale, counts, releases slow. The room copies his rhythm without meaning to, and the silence starts carrying his fingerprint. Twice. Part 3: Tension in the Corners Marcus leans against the steel table, smoke curling from his blunt, eyes fixed on his crew. ‚ÄúYou all know the rules,‚Äù he says low, each word deliberate. ‚ÄúRespect. Loyalty. No mistakes. One slip, and this whole empire cracks.‚Äù One of the younger goons shifts nervously, avoiding Marcus‚Äôs eyes. Another clears his throat like he wants to speak, but doesn‚Äôt. Camera angle: close on Marcus‚Äôs eyes narrowing. A slow zoom, suspicion tightening. He taps ash onto the floor. ‚ÄúSay what‚Äôs on your chest, or get out my sight.‚Äù The soundtrack drops into silence‚Äîlike the block holding its breath. In the corner, a fan chops the air into thin slices. A fly rides the blade, makes a tiny halo, vanishes. The kid with the nervous shoes finally finds words. ‚ÄúNumbers feel heavy tonight,‚Äù he mutters. Marcus tilts his head. ‚ÄúHeavy means you ain‚Äôt ready.‚Äù The door groans somewhere in the dark, a hinge remembering last winter. He nods at Darnell. ‚ÄúCheck the perimeter. Twice.‚Äù Darnell moves. The camera follows his shadow to a slit of night beneath the loading bay. Marcus turns back to the table, lays palms on cold steel, and the room remembers who taught it to be quiet. Part 4: The Ambush The silence shatters. A door creaks. Heavy boots echo on concrete. Then‚Äîbang! The warehouse door bursts open, metal screaming. Red-and-blue flashes spill in like blood across the floor. ‚ÄúFEDERAL AGENTS! DON‚ÄôT MOVE!‚Äù Camera whips fast: goons scatter. Rifles raised. Cash spilling. Bricks tumbling. Marcus doesn‚Äôt flinch. He exhales smoke, slow, calm, even as chaos detonates around him. ‚ÄúBurn it!‚Äù he roars. One of his men kicks over a barrel. Flames lick high, swallowing kilos, swallowing evidence. Gunfire erupts, ricochets sparking off steel beams. Quick cuts‚Äîmuzzle flashes, agents shouting, goons yelling. The scene blurs into pure chaos.  Sprinklers sputter, cough, give up. The floor becomes a mirror of fire and broken plastic. Marcus slides behind a stack, returns three shots, moves left, returns two more. Darnell yanks a recruit down by the collar, saves his life and loses his hat. A flashbang blooms white; sound folds; everyone forgets their own names for half a breath. ‚ÄúSouth exit!‚Äù Marcus barks. A shutter grinds halfway, jams. He rips a crowbar from a crate, wedges, levers, curses. Metal screams, then yields. ‚ÄúMove!‚Äù he orders, and the camera finds his face through smoke, unblinking, carved from the same steel. Sirens growl closer outside. Part 5: Betrayal in the Smoke Camera: handheld, shaky, pushing through the smoke and bullets. Marcus ducks behind crates, gun in hand, eyes scanning. Then he sees it‚Äîone of his own, whispering to a man in a suit. An earpiece glints under the flashing lights. A CI. Marcus‚Äôs chest tightens, rage burning. He shouts over the gunfire: ‚ÄúYou sold us out!‚Äù The traitor freezes, guilt flashing across his face for a second before he bolts for the exit. Marcus fires‚Äîthe shot echoes louder than the others, cutting through the chaos. The camera zooms on Marcus‚Äôs face, jaw clenched, smoke and fire swirling around him. Voiceover, gritty: ‚ÄúOn the block‚Ä¶ survival don‚Äôt mean living. It means killing what‚Äôs killing you.‚Äù The CI stumbles, grabs a pillar, leaves a red handprint like a signature he can‚Äôt take back. Agents surge; somebody yells ‚ÄúClear!‚Äù too early and eats a ricochet. Marcus pivots, empties the mag, swaps, breath. He points at the burning stacks. ‚ÄúLet it all die,‚Äù he orders. Darnell nods, eyes hard, herds two soldiers through the gap in the shutter. Marcus backs toward the darkness, smoke wrapping him like a cape. The screen smears to black as alarms scream, and the warehouse forgets their names.

message.text:
Here's a Sneak Peek.

PROLOGUE ‚Äî SHADOWS AIN‚ÄôT SILENT
Night hangs low over the city like a hood pulled tight.
 Streetlights flicker ‚Äî tired eyes refusing to sleep.
 Somewhere a siren weeps into the dark, echoing a truth nobody admits:
On this block, quiet is never peace.
 Quiet is set-up.
A figure moves through alley steam ‚Äî slow, controlled, like violence wearing sneakers. Cigarette glow pulses like a heartbeat refusing to die. Every corner whispers Marcus Reed‚Äôs name. Not loud. Not proud. Tentative. Afraid.
Up above, a rooftop door cracks open.
 A shadow watches.
 Patient.
 Hungry.
A text vibrates in Marcus‚Äôs pocket.
 Private number.
 No contact picture.
Three words:
 YOU‚ÄôRE NEXT.
Marcus doesn‚Äôt freeze.
 He‚Äôs been next his whole life.
He crushes the cigarette against brick.
 Smoke ghosts away.
 Concrete groans under his boots.
 Somewhere, a window shuts like a secret learning to keep itself.
The block inhales.
Marcus exhales.
Game‚Äôs already started.
Welcome back.

CHAPTER 1 ‚Äì WAREHOUSE SHADOWS
Part 1: Smoke and Steel 
The camera glides low across a warehouse floor slick with oil stains and cigarette butts. Fluorescent lights flicker overhead like they‚Äôre on their last breath. Stacks of cocaine bricks sit wrapped tight in plastic, piled high like cursed treasure.
 The soundtrack hums low: a heavy bass line, thumping slow, like a heartbeat that knows something‚Äôs coming.
 Marcus Reed steps into frame. The glow of his blunt lights his face for half a second‚Äîhard jaw, eyes sharp, smoke curling like whispers.
 Goons move in the background. One seals bags. Another slams diesel truck doors shut. Rifles glint in the half-light.
 ‚ÄúCount it twice,‚Äù Marcus mutters, his voice steady but cold. ‚ÄúLast man that shorted me ain‚Äôt walking no more.‚Äù
 The room stills for a beat. Even the scales seem louder as the numbers flicker green.
 He taps ash, scans rafters, notes the ladder that wasn‚Äôt there yesterday. A fan ticks, off rhythm, like a bad omen with loose screws.
 Camera pushes in on Marcus‚Äôs hands‚Äîscarred, sure, calm like street weather. He doesn‚Äôt blink when a pallet pops; he only shifts his weight and smiles without joy, the smile you practice when danger starts spelling your name in smoke. Tonight.

Part 2: The Silent Weigh-In 
Close-up: hands, rough and scarred, sliding kilo after kilo onto digital scales. Each beep cuts the silence sharper than a blade.
 Marcus circles the table like a director on set. Every move, every breath, he watches.
 ‚ÄúBag tighter,‚Äù he snaps at one goon fumbling with tape. ‚ÄúYou leave air in there, you might as well sign your death certificate.‚Äù
 The man nods fast, sweat running down his temple.
 Overhead shot: crates stacked against the wall. A shadow moves in the rafters. Quick cut‚Äîgone before anyone notices.
 The bass in the soundtrack climbs higher.
 A stopwatch clicks. Numbers glow cold on a wall clock that‚Äôs always three minutes fast; Marcus keeps it that way, likes getting to trouble before trouble gets to him.
 He lifts a brick, squeezes, listens for that soft crunch that tells the truth. It purrs. He nods.
 The camera lingers on a scale drifting a gram, drifting back‚Äîlike it‚Äôs breathing. ‚ÄúSwap it,‚Äù he orders. ‚ÄúBad lungs.‚Äù
 A forklift coughs awake then dies. Somewhere a phone vibrates.
 Marcus inhales, tastes plastic and promise. He holds the exhale, counts, releases slow. The room copies his rhythm without meaning to, and the silence starts carrying his fingerprint. Twice.

Part 3: Tension in the Corners 
Marcus leans against the steel table, smoke curling from his blunt, eyes fixed on his crew.
 ‚ÄúYou all know the rules,‚Äù he says low, each word deliberate. ‚ÄúRespect. Loyalty. No mistakes. One slip, and this whole empire cracks.‚Äù
 One of the younger goons shifts nervously, avoiding Marcus‚Äôs eyes. Another clears his throat like he wants to speak, but doesn‚Äôt.
 Camera angle: close on Marcus‚Äôs eyes narrowing. A slow zoom, suspicion tightening.
 He taps ash onto the floor. ‚ÄúSay what‚Äôs on your chest, or get out my sight.‚Äù
 The soundtrack drops into silence‚Äîlike the block holding its breath.
 In the corner, a fan chops the air into thin slices. A fly rides the blade, makes a tiny halo, vanishes.
 The kid with the nervous shoes finally finds words. ‚ÄúNumbers feel heavy tonight,‚Äù he mutters.
 Marcus tilts his head. ‚ÄúHeavy means you ain‚Äôt ready.‚Äù
 The door groans somewhere in the dark, a hinge remembering last winter.
 He nods at Darnell. ‚ÄúCheck the perimeter. Twice.‚Äù
 Darnell moves. The camera follows his shadow to a slit of night beneath the loading bay.
 Marcus turns back to the table, lays palms on cold steel, and the room remembers who taught it to be quiet.

Part 4: The Ambush 
The silence shatters.
 A door creaks. Heavy boots echo on concrete. Then‚Äîbang! The warehouse door bursts open, metal screaming. Red-and-blue flashes spill in like blood across the floor.
 ‚ÄúFEDERAL AGENTS! DON‚ÄôT MOVE!‚Äù
 Camera whips fast: goons scatter. Rifles raised. Cash spilling. Bricks tumbling.
 Marcus doesn‚Äôt flinch. He exhales smoke, slow, calm, even as chaos detonates around him.
 ‚ÄúBurn it!‚Äù he roars.
 One of his men kicks over a barrel. Flames lick high, swallowing kilos, swallowing evidence. Gunfire erupts, ricochets sparking off steel beams.
 Quick cuts‚Äîmuzzle flashes, agents shouting, goons yelling. The scene blurs into pure chaos.
 Sprinklers sputter, cough, give up. The floor becomes a mirror of fire and broken plastic.
 Marcus slides behind a stack, returns three shots, moves left, returns two more.
 Darnell yanks a recruit down by the collar, saves his life and loses his hat.
 A flashbang blooms white; sound folds; everyone forgets their own names for half a breath.
 ‚ÄúSouth exit!‚Äù Marcus barks. A shutter grinds halfway, jams.
 He rips a crowbar from a crate, wedges, levers, curses. Metal screams, then yields.
 ‚ÄúMove!‚Äù he orders, and the camera finds his face through smoke, unblinking, carved from the same steel. Sirens growl closer outside.

Part 5: Betrayal in the Smoke 
Camera: handheld, shaky, pushing through the smoke and bullets.
 Marcus ducks behind crates, gun in hand, eyes scanning.
 Then he sees it‚Äîone of his own, whispering to a man in a suit. An earpiece glints under the flashing lights.
 A CI.
 Marcus‚Äôs chest tightens, rage burning. He shouts over the gunfire: ‚ÄúYou sold us out!‚Äù
 The traitor freezes, guilt flashing across his face for a second before he bolts for the exit.
 Marcus fires‚Äîthe shot echoes louder than the others, cutting through the chaos.
 The camera zooms on Marcus‚Äôs face, jaw clenched, smoke and fire swirling around him.
 Voiceover, gritty: ‚ÄúOn the block‚Ä¶ survival don‚Äôt mean living. It means killing what‚Äôs killing you.‚Äù
 The CI stumbles, grabs a pillar, leaves a red handprint like a signature he can‚Äôt take back.
 Agents surge; somebody yells ‚ÄúClear!‚Äù too early and eats a ricochet.
 Marcus pivots, empties the mag, swaps, breath.
 He points at the burning stacks. ‚ÄúLet it all die,‚Äù he orders.
 Darnell nods, eyes hard, herds two soldiers through the gap in the shutter.
 Marcus backs toward the darkness, smoke wrapping him like a cape.
 The screen smears to black as alarms scream, and the warehouse forgets their names.

items.text:
New dates added - Dec 8-19 in Las Vegas. To book go to https://rebrand.ly/freehdsht

FREE HEADSHOT and 1-HOUR SESSION ‚Äì East Summerlin, Las Vegas

Address sent automatically after booking

Hi! I‚Äôm Steve Fogarty, a Las Vegas headshot specialist and owner of EXPO TRAFFIC, where we run large-scale headshot activations for major trade shows (600-700 people over 2.5 days).

I‚Äôm currently testing new lighting setups and posing flows for upcoming conventions, and I‚Äôm looking for real people to sit for practice sessions in a more relaxed environment. In return for your time, you get a full headshot session and one professional, retouched headshot for free.

**What You Get**
* A 60‚Äì75 minute headshot session
* Multiple looks + lighting setups
* A private online gallery
* One edited, retouched image included
* Additional images optional (zero pressure)

**Examples of my retouching**

[https://rebrand.ly/retouching](https://rebrand.ly/retouching)

Why There‚Äôs a $20 Fee

It‚Äôs not a sales charge. It‚Äôs a **non-refundable security deposit and show-up guarantee** that ensures the schedule stays reliable for both of us. The $20 simply confirms your commitment to attend ‚Äî and your favorite image is still included for free.

How You Get Your Image

After the session:
* We will review your images, and you'll tell me which ones are your favorites that you do not want deleted.
* I will edit and retouch your favorites, then upload them to your private gallery.
* You can download your favorite image using a coupon code (provided).
* You‚Äôre welcome to purchase extras, but it‚Äôs totally optional.

What to Expect / How to Prepare
* Arrive camera-ready (mirror + restroom available)
* Plan for 3‚Äì4 different looks
* Avoid pure white tops if possible
* Relax ‚Äî I‚Äôll guide you through every pose and expression

Safety + Professionalism
* All public areas are video security-monitored for your comfort and safety
* Private areas (bathrooms, changing areas) are never recorded
* References available by request

You can preview my work here:

[https://www.expotraffic.com/headshots/las-vegas-headshots](https://www.expotraffic.com/headshots/las-vegas-headshots)

**Location**

**East Summerlin near Rainbow & Alta**

**Exact address provided after booking.**

FREE HEADSHOT and 1-HOUR SESSION ‚Äì East Summerlin, Las Vegas

Address sent automatically after booking

Hi! I‚Äôm Steve Fogarty, a Las Vegas headshot specialist and owner of EXPO TRAFFIC, where we run large-scale headshot activations for major trade shows (600-700 people over 2.5 days).

I‚Äôm currently testing new lighting setups and posing flows for upcoming conventions, and I‚Äôm looking for real people to sit for practice sessions in a more relaxed environment. In return for your time, you get a full headshot session and one professional, retouched headshot for free.

**What You Get**
* A 60‚Äì75 minute headshot session
* Multiple looks + lighting setups
* A private online gallery
* One edited, retouched image included
* Additional images optional (zero pressure)

**Examples of my retouching**

[https://rebrand.ly/retouching](https://rebrand.ly/retouching)

Why There‚Äôs a $20 Fee

It‚Äôs not a sales charge. It‚Äôs a **non-refundable security deposit and show-up guarantee** that ensures the schedule stays reliable for both of us. The $20 simply confirms your commitment to attend ‚Äî and your favorite image is still included for free.

How You Get Your Image

After the session:
* We will review your images, and you'll tell me which ones are your favorites that you do not want deleted.
* I will edit and retouch your favorites, then upload them to your private gallery.
* You can download your favorite image using a coupon code (provided).
* You‚Äôre welcome to purchase extras, but it‚Äôs totally optional.

What to Expect / How to Prepare
* Arrive camera-ready (mirror + restroom available)
* Plan for 3‚Äì4 different looks
* Avoid pure white tops if possible
* Relax ‚Äî I‚Äôll guide you through every pose and expression

Safety + Professionalism
* All public areas are video security-monitored for your comfort and safety
* Private areas (bathrooms, changing areas) are never recorded
* References available by request

You can preview my work here:

[https://www.expotraffic.com/headshots/las-vegas-headshots](https://www.expotraffic.com/headshots/las-vegas-headshots)

**Location**

**East Summerlin near Rainbow & Alta**

**Exact address provided after booking.**

**Looking forward to creating something great together!**

**‚Äì Steve Fogarty**

**Owner ‚Äì STEVEN JOSEPH PHOTOGRAPHY | EXPO TRAFFIC HEADSHOTS**

items.text:
Questions.
1. What do you do if you don't have a show reel?
2. How do you make a show reel, or the best way to make one? Software?

topComments.text: There are decent showreel companies out there who'll create one for you using 3 or 4 different scripted scenarios. Certainly a good idea if you don't have any or few credits to choose from

You can easily do a self-taped scene to work as a showreel when you're starting out. There's plenty of advice online about setting up a basic self-tape. Find a scene that resonates with you, and that works for your playing age and acting strengths. Ask a friend to read the other character, but keep them out of the shot. Duologues are better than monologues, as they show you listening and responding 'in the moment'. Casting directors want to see you clearly, hear you clearly and get a feel for your skill level and suitability for a role. They don't expect actors at the start of their journey to have slick, professional reels.

items.text:
Hi everyone!

I'm the producer of an upcoming student short film, called Necrotic Anonymous. A psychological thriller. We're currently looking for actors to join our project.

‚Äî‚Äî ‚Äî‚Äî - - 

üé≠ Requirements:

Katie Williams - Playing Age 19-21 Female

Dr. Paige - Playing Age 25-30 Any Gender

Benny - Playing Age 20-25 Male

‚Äî‚Äî ‚Äî‚Äî - - 

üóìÔ∏è Important Dates:

Deadline for applying is the 1st January and Auditions will be held on the 5th January at Futureworks University 

‚Äî‚Äî ‚Äî‚Äî - - 

üìçLocation: 

Filming will take place in February across multiple

locations in Manchester/Salford

‚Äî‚Äî ‚Äî‚Äî - - 

üí∏ Unpaid:

As this is a student production, roles are unpaid, but we will cover travel expenses and provide full catering on set.

Our aim is to create a high-quality short film to submit to festivals such as the Manchester Independent Film Festival and Bolton Film Festival.

If you're interested in getting involved or would like more details about the roles, please drop a message or comment below. We'd love to hear from you!

‚Äî‚Äî ‚Äî‚Äî - - 

Here's the form link to apply:

https://forms.gle/2HPgeoefjsGphrmG8

Hi everyone,
I‚Äôm Mohamed Redha Zertal, Liverpool-based with a strong on-camera presence and real performance experience. 
I‚Äôm looking to collaborate on short films, drama pieces, and character-led projects across Liverpool, Manchester, and Salford.

What I bring:
‚Ä¢ Strong screen presence
‚Ä¢ Stand-up comedy experience (Hot Water Comedy Club)
‚Ä¢ Confident delivery + natural timing
‚Ä¢ Multilingual: Arabic, French, English
‚Ä¢ Athletic look ‚Äî ideal for police, detective, action, villain, father, security, or emotional drama roles
‚Ä¢ Reliable, disciplined, takes direction well
‚Ä¢ Comfortable with emotional scenes and dialogue-heavy roles

Availability:
‚Ä¢ Immediate
‚Ä¢ Flexible for rehearsals & shoot days
‚Ä¢ Same-day self-tapes

I can provide:
‚Ä¢ Professional headshots
‚Ä¢ 20‚Äì30 sec intro/showreel clip
‚Ä¢ Self-tape for any role
‚Ä¢ Full acting CV

If you need someone who shows up prepared, delivers, and treats your film seriously, feel free to message me.

Looking forward to working with talented filmmakers.
‚Äì Redha üé¨

sharedPost.text:
the wait is over! we are now accepting submissions for our summer production of ‚ÄúBe More Chill!‚Äù

for full details, visit the link in our bio.

Simone Nathalia - Director/Choreographer
Taylor McKee - Music Director
Madison Raybould - Choreographer
Morgan Da Silva-Rolph - Stage Manager

Music and Lyrics by Joe Iconis
Book by Joe Tracz
Based on the Novel by Ned Vizzini

audition dates
in-person: December 20th & 21st, 2025
callbacks: January 3rd, 2026
self-tapes: submissions due on Dec. 19th

audition venue:
Carousel Theatre for Young People, 1411 Cartwright St, Granville Island

audition requirements:
all roles in this production are volunteer, non-union. xoxo welcomes performers 18+ of all genders, ethnicities, and skill levels to audition.

what to prepare:
1. 2 contrasting musical theatre songs, (you may only be asked to sing one, but please have both ready).

2. a 1-2 minute contemporary, comedic monologue - this must be memorized.

how to apply:
please email your headshot and resume to theatre@xoxotv.ca to be scheduled with an audition time, or to request a self-tape submission.

character breakdowns can be found in our ‚Äúaudition package‚Äù link in bio.

production dates:
July 15th - 18th, 2026

production venue:
Firehall Arts Centre, 280 E Cordova St, Vancouver

notes:
rehearsals will begin April 30th, 2026
Saturdays 10:00am to 6:00pm
Tuesdays & Thursdays 6:00pm to 10:00pm

contact info@xoxotv.ca or DM us with any questions!

best of luck to all performers - we‚Äôll see you at auditions! üòÅüíÑüêæ

BE MORE CHILL is presented by arrangement with Concord Theatricals.
www.concordtheatricals.com
The world premiere production of Be More Chill was commissioned and originally produced by Two River Theater Company in Red Bank, NJ
John Dias, Artistic Director / Michael Hurst, Managing Director
This work was supported by a Theatre Commissioning and Production Initiative grant from the Doris Duke Charitable Foundation
Orchestrations and Arrangements by Charlie Rosen
.

Female, 16‚Äì18 age-presenting (actor must be 18+)

Luka‚Äôs older sister. Loud, messy, protective, insecure underneath. Pretends she‚Äôs tough but she‚Äôs still figuring life out.

items.text:
**CASTING CALL FOR A 10-MIN SHORT FILM**
Hi everyone! We‚Äôre seeking local actors for a neorealist short film shooting in late January in Vancouver. The film is intended for 2026 festival submissions.

**Logline:**

A college student volunteers on a visual-assist app to help an elderly man in his small apartment, unaware that a quiet glitch has turned their private calls into a public stream.

**Production Details**

‚Ä¢ Location: Vancouver, BC

‚Ä¢ Shoot Window: Late January ‚Äì Early February 2026 (TBD)

‚Ä¢ Genre: Neorealist Drama

‚Ä¢ Non-Union / Volunteer

‚Ä¢ Meals + IMDb credit provided

**ROLES**

**MAYA ‚Äî Female, 19‚Äì24 (Open Ethnicity)**

Quiet, inward, emotionally guarded.
Minimal dialogue; performance driven by micro-reactions and natural handheld close-ups.
Must be comfortable with subtle, restrained acting.
Grounded student under stress ‚Äî *Wendy & Lucy*, *Never Rarely Sometimes Always* tone.

**LEON ‚Äî Male, 65‚Äì80 (Open Ethnicity)**

Soft-spoken, solitary, dignified.
Partially visually impaired; actor need not be visually impaired but must portray limited vision naturally.
Understated physicality: small gestures, hesitation, lived-in presence.

**TO APPLY**

Please send the following to **seetogetherfilm@gmail.com**
Subject: **‚ÄúSEE TOGETHER ‚Äì MAYA‚Äù** or **‚ÄúSEE TOGETHER ‚Äì LEON‚Äù**
‚Ä¢ Recent headshot
‚Ä¢ Short introduction (video or written)
‚Ä¢ Availability (Jan‚ÄìFeb 2026)
‚Ä¢ Any naturalistic acting samples (if available)

We will cast people first through self-tapes.

Thank you!

**Mini serial  wojenny 1940 ‚Äì Kobieta, cywil francuski**

** **

Nasza Gliwicka Grupa Pasjonat√≥w **‚Äò‚ÄôGrupa1940‚Äô‚Äô ** kobietƒô  w wieku 25 ‚Äì 30 do roli francuskiej kobiety. Postaƒá kobiety bƒôdzie pokazana w jednym z odcink√≥w podczas ataku Niemc√≥w na budynek cywilny. Razem z mƒô≈ºem bƒôdƒÖ chcieƒá uciekaƒá z dymiƒÖcego siƒô mieszkania. Oczywi≈õcie sƒÖ przewidziane po 2 kwestie w jezyku francuskim. Zdjƒôcie poni≈ºej jest naszym materia≈Çem z test√≥w tej sceny.

 

Szukamy os√≥b be≈º tatua≈ºy, bez farbowanych w≈Ços√≥w czy d≈Çugich paznokciach.  Je≈õli chodzi o kostiumy to my je bƒôdziemy  wydawaƒá.  Szukamy os√≥b g≈Ç√≥wnie z Gliwic i okolic (Zabrze, Katowice). Szukamy francuskich cywili, kt√≥rzy bƒôdƒÖ atakowani przez niemiecki odzia≈Ç.

 

**Na wiosnƒô roku 2026 planujemy realizacje zdjƒôc do tego **projektu. Bƒôdziemy realizowaƒá mini serial oparty o wƒÖtki grupy okultystycznej ‚Äô‚Äô**Ahnenerbe‚Äô**‚Äô kt√≥ra chce zdobyƒá s≈Çynne artefakty ale w tym kto≈õ im chce przeszkadzaƒá. Projekt a siƒô sk≈Çadaƒá z 6 odcink√≥w po 10/12 minut ka≈ºdy. Bƒôdziemy te≈º sukcesywnie dodawaƒá inne og≈Çoszenia zwiƒÖzane z tym projektem. Mile widziane zdjƒôcia aktualne. Na zdjƒôciu powy≈ºej osoba bƒôdzie mieƒá podobny kostium.** **Umieszczone materia≈Çy sƒÖ z naszej sesji.** Nie bƒôdzie to zlecenie p≈Çatne.**

 

Od 01.04.25 za≈Ço≈ºyli≈õmy sw√≥j kana≈Ç na portalu youtube z filmami z naszych plan√≥w ≈ºeby mo≈ºna by≈Ço zobaczyƒá jak to u nas wyglƒÖda od kuchni. 

 

https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCE8KyfwpyFGzzwUDqdwy74g

 

**Nie bƒôdzie to zlecenie p≈Çatne.**

 

Wiƒôcej informacji na Priv

**Serial nie jest stworzony z sympatii do tej nazistowskiej organizacji lecz wynika to z samego scenariusza aby ukaza≈Ç zbrodnie i sam fakt i≈º by≈Ça w pe≈Çni z≈Ça. W produkcji znajdƒÖ siƒô osoby, kt√≥re bƒôdƒÖ chcieƒá walczyƒá i potƒôpiaƒá te wielkie z≈Ço jakim by≈Ç nazizm. W oparciu o Dz.U.2017.0.2204 t.j. - Ustawa z dnia 6 czerwca 1997 r. - Kodeks karny,Art. 256 "Propagowanie faszyzmu lub innego ustroju totalitarnego lub nawo≈Çywanie domnienawi≈õci", ¬ß3 - nie narusza prawa proponujƒÖc przedmiot do cel√≥w historycznych lub kolekcjonerskich.**

Hi everyone,
I‚Äôm Mohamed Redha Zertal, Liverpool-based with a strong on-camera presence and real performance experience. 
I‚Äôm looking to collaborate on short films, drama pieces, and character-led projects across Liverpool, Manchester, and Salford.

What I bring:
‚Ä¢ Strong screen presence
‚Ä¢ Stand-up comedy experience (Hot Water Comedy Club)
‚Ä¢ Confident delivery + natural timing
‚Ä¢ Multilingual: Arabic, French, English
‚Ä¢ Athletic look ‚Äî ideal for police, detective, action, villain, father, security, or emotional drama roles
‚Ä¢ Reliable, disciplined, takes direction well
‚Ä¢ Comfortable with emotional scenes and dialogue-heavy roles

Availability:
‚Ä¢ Immediate
‚Ä¢ Flexible for rehearsals & shoot days
‚Ä¢ Same-day self-tapes

I can provide:
‚Ä¢ Professional headshots
‚Ä¢ 20‚Äì30 sec intro/showreel clip
‚Ä¢ Self-tape for any role
‚Ä¢ Full acting CV

If you need someone who shows up prepared, delivers, and treats your film seriously, feel free to message me.

Looking forward to working with talented filmmakers.
‚Äì Redha üé¨

We are casting for the 2026 Weird and Wonderful festival which will run between March 3rd and March 8th.

‚ÄúSardines‚Äù follows five sardines as they bicker over life's meaning and their purpose in the world. 

We are looking for 5 actors of any age or look who can comfortably play off of each others comedic timing.

If you are interested in auditioning for a role please send a self tape that you feel fits the criteria via we transfer / any other downloadable link to:

Seanrobinsonfreelance@gmail.com

Self tapes are due by 31st December and the cast will be contacted by the new year.

Please note: this is a 20 min play and will be part of a three play evening. A profit share will be paid.

Do serialu Gliniarze szukam ( PILNE!!!)
1. Kamil Marciszek (18) ‚Äì typ romantyka i rockowca. Spotyka siƒô z MartynƒÖ. Ubiera siƒô w ramoneskƒô, jeansy i glany. U≈õmiechniƒôty, przebojowy i wyluzowany. Niezbyt analizuje fakty. TERMIN: 17.12 i 18.12, STAWKA: 900 z≈Ç netto za 2 dni
2. Artur Kawalec (18) ‚Äì ucze≈Ñ, typ sportowca. By≈Çy ch≈Çopak Ani. Ubiera siƒô w polo i jeansy. Porywczy, energiczny, wygadany, sprytny i uczuciowy. Nie pogodzi≈Ç siƒô z tym, ≈ºe Ania go zostawi≈Ça i nienawidzi siebie za to, ≈ºe jƒÖ pobi≈Ç. TERMIN: 17.12 i 18.12, STAWKA: 900 z≈Ç netto za 2 dni
3. Robert Kubalski (21) ‚Äì kucharz, chodzi≈Ç do tej samej szko≈Çy co Ania i pozostali uczniowie. Z charakteru jest dra≈ºliwy. Ubiera siƒô przebojowo ‚Äì w kolorowe koszule. Raz da≈Ç siƒô nam√≥wiƒá na rozb√≥j, ale wpad≈Ç i ma wyrok w zawiasach. Pracuje jako kucharz. TERMIN: 17,18,19. 12, STAWKA: 1050 z≈Ç netto za 3 dni
4. Pawe≈Ç Zajdel (23) ‚Äì student matematyki, praktykant w szkole. Potajemnie spotyka siƒô i romansuje z AniƒÖ, kt√≥rƒÖ bardzo kocha. Na og√≥≈Ç to spokojny romantyk i nerd, jednak w odcinku jest na skraju za≈Çamania nerwowego. Ubiera siƒô w jeansy, T-shirt i marynarkƒô. TERMIN: 17,18,19. 12, STAWKA: 1050 z≈Ç netto za 3 dni
5. Wsp√≥≈Çlokator (23) ‚Äì typ nerda, ubiera siƒô wygodnie. TERMIN: 18.12, STAWKA: 250 z≈Ç netto
6. Wychowawczyni (31) ‚Äì Izabela Wicher. Nauczycielka geografii. Sumienna, oddana uczniom wychowawczyni. Ubiera siƒô w boj√≥wki, buty trekkingowe i koszule w kwiaty. TERMIN: 17.12, STAWKA: 350 z≈Ç netto

CASTING CALL ‚Äì Independent Short Film (LONDON)

We are casting for an upcoming student short film exploring obsession, ambition, and the dark side of the ballet world.

Production: Student film via The American University of Rome

Director: Maxine Sutton

Cinematographer: Georgia Blackson

Shooting Dates: December 12‚Äì19

ROLES

NATASHA (Lead)

Female, 18‚Äì28

Ballet-trained (advanced preferred)

Must convey vulnerability, intensity, and psychological depth

Strong acting, presence, and physical performance required

Slavic accent preferred.

Pay: 250‚Ç¨ flat rate for entire production

RUDOLPH

Male, 25‚Äì40

Dance experience preferred

Embodies both beauty and cruelty ‚Äî a man who inspires awe, fear, and complete submission.

Slavic accent preferred.

Pay: 250‚Ç¨ flat rate for entire production

SYNOPSIS

Natasha, a talented but tormented ballerina, navigates a high-stakes audition that tests the limits of her physical and psychological endurance. As she strives for perfection under the watchful eye of the enigmatic Rudolph, the line between reality and terror begins to blur, forcing her to confront the true cost of ambition.

TO APPLY

Please complete the audition form and send it, along with a headshot, to: maxineclairesutton@gmail.com

+++EXKLUSIVER SCHAUSPIEL-WORKSHOP f√ºr QUEREINSTEIGER*INNEN+++

(NUR NOCH 3 FREIE PL√ÑTZE! - Stand: 06.12.2025)

#schauspielworkshop #quereinsteiger #schauspielquereinsteiger #quereinsteigerworkshop #cameraacting #arbeitsworkshop #showreel #aboutme #film #tv #exklusiv #engelspostmanagement

Aufgrund der gro√üen Nachfrage veranstalte ich im JANUAR 2026 (09.-11.01.+16.-18.01.2026 / 2 WE) einen EXKLUSIVEN, 6-T√ÑGIGEN Schauspiel-Workshop f√ºr QUEREINSTEIGER*INNEN. Die Inhalte k√∂nnt Ihr dem Flyer entnehmen. 

Quereinsteiger*innen haben wenig M√∂glichkeiten auf dem deutschen Markt, weshalb ich mich dazu entschieden habe, ein sinnvolles, n√ºtzliches Angebot auf den Markt zu bringen. 

Es handelt sich um einen PRAXISORIENTIERTEN Workshop, was bedeutet, in welchem mit den Teilnehmenden an der Performance gearbeitet wird, u. a. durch Szenenarbeit, E-/Live-Casting-Situationen, Camera-Acting etc. Au√üerdem erhalten die Teilnehmenden alle wichtigen Informationen rund um das Thema "Selbstmarketing" - zusammen mit wertvollen Tipps und Tricks. 

Zus√§tzlich produzieren wir eine professionelle SHOWREELSZENE f√ºr jeden Teilnehmenden, welche wir in dem 6-t√§gigen Workshop vorbereiten (*WICHTIGE INFO: Die Produktion der Szenen findet au√üerhalb des Workshops statt. sharedPost.text:
üéÑ‚ú® What can a small team create when human imagination meets AI?

Over the past few weeks, we‚Äôve been working with a small creative team on something that started as a simple experiment‚Ä¶ and grew into a full multi-genre music video collection called "The Hope Multiverse - Vol. 1."

Every video began with a human idea, emotion, or story we wanted to express.

AI helped us bring those ideas to life in cinematic, playful, and sometimes totally unexpected ways.

A fun twist for early December:
Two of the favorites so far are Christmas songs - one ‚Äúsung‚Äù by a baby, and one performed by an original AI pop singer. Both somehow feel warm, joyful, and surprisingly human.

The playlist spans an entire mini-universe of concepts:

 üé® Van Gogh‚Äôs self-portrait singing an art-inspired ballad

 üåô An anime girl finding calm after digital burnout

 üõ∏ A UFO satire teasing ‚Äúnothing to see here‚Äù secrecy

 üê¶ A real backyard bird inspiring a song about courage

 üîß A kid inventor‚Äôs chaotic (and heartfelt) pop anthem

All of this came from a small team exploring one question I care deeply about: What happens when humans lead the creative vision - and AI expands what‚Äôs possible?

And just to be clear:
We aren‚Äôt associated with any AI platforms.

If you‚Äôre curious how storytelling is evolving - or if you want some early-December holiday spirit - I‚Äôd love for you to explore the playlist and read the video descriptions. Each one explains how the idea started, how the visuals and music came together, and how human creativity guided the entire process.

Would love to hear which piece surprises you the most. üéß‚ú®

üëâ Watch the 12 music videos here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLX6tC4WGOeiMwZAZTEh-1UCyMhscLfD0W
